cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper is about a neural ranking model for information retrieval that incorporates knowledge graphs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of knowledge graphs involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the representation and storage of data, which could also place it in cs.DB (Databases).
